    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>In Java 11 we can use <code>Collection.toArray(generator)</code> method. The following code will create a new array of String:</p>\n\n<pre><code>Set&lt;String&gt; set = Set.of(\"one\", \"two\", \"three\");\nString[] array = set.toArray(String[]::new)\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>See: <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/11/docs/api/java.base/java/util/Collection.html#toArray(java.util.function.IntFunction)\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/11/docs/api/java.base/java/util/Collection.html#toArray(java.util.function.IntFunction)</a></p>\n"
  }, {
